Japan’s Keizai Doyukai Welcomes Noda as DPJ Leader

-- B y   K a n o k o   M a t s u y a m a
-- 
2011-08-30T00:18:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/japan-s-keizai-doyukai-welcomes-noda-as-dpj-leader-correct-.html
(Corrects story published yesterday to fix quote from
Hasegawa in first paragraph.)  The head of the Japan Association of
Corporate Executives, or Keizai Doyukai, said he welcomes the
election of a "fresh" leader after Yoshihiko Noda was chosen as
head of the ruling  Democratic Party .  Yasuchika Hasegawa, leader of the nation’s second-biggest
business lobby, said he wants to cooperate with Noda to return
the nation to steady economic growth. He spoke to reporters in
Tokyo after Noda was chosen to replace outgoing Prime Minister
 Naoto Kan .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kanoko Matsuyama in Tokyo at 
 kmatsuyama2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gearoid Reidy at 
 greidy1@bloomberg.net  